BAUCHI – A chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Bauchi State, Ukkasha Hamza Rahama, has called on the Commissioner of Police and the Director of the Department of State Security (DSS) in the state to fish the sponsors of political thugs who carry out the destruction of campaign billboards of aspirants contesting under the platform of the party. Addressing newsmen in Bauchi on Wednesday Ukkasha condemned the ugly situation in the state, saying that the reoccurrence of such development will only succeed in pitching political parties against each other. He said that Bauchi state has been at the forefront of political activities in the country in terms of elections and federal appointments, hence a negative development such as this, will not augur well for the political activities in the state. -Advertisement- “It is in the light of this development, that I see the need to draw the attention of his Excellency, the Executive Governor of Bauchi State, Senator Bala Mohammed to the urgent need to address the increasing attacks on the All Progressives Congress in the state, especially as we are approaching the general elections to come 2023. “The scenes of destruction of billboards and campaign posters of Nura Manu Soro led by unknown persons stand condemned and unfortunate. This is coming at the time the said Nura Manu Soro has every constitutional right to contest any political seat he seems fit. “On no account should a citizen of the state be cowed or intimidated into not contesting any political position due to the activities of thugs and their sponsors by destroying campaign materials,” he said.